"script": "A scientist sat a four-year-old in front of a single marshmallow and made a strange promise. If the child could wait fifteen minutes without eating it, they'd get two instead. Then he left the room. Some kids devoured it the second the door closed. But others covered their eyes, sang songs, even sat on their hands to resist. And here's the twist. Decades later, the kids who waited had better grades, better jobs, and healthier lives. You see, it was never about candy. It quietly measured self-control, the one tiny trait that shapes almost everything you'll ever become.",
